ontent">
<h1 id=3D"user-content-tools-installation-guide-for-developer-workstation-s=
et-up">Tools installation guide for developer workstation set-up</h1>
<p>This guide describes how to install tools required for the set-up of a d=
eveloper's workstation (with Windows 10 or 11).</p>
<h3 id=3D"user-content-chocolatey-installation">Chocolatey Installation</h3=
>
<p>To install the Mesh Developer Tool prerequisites we recommend using Choc=
olatey (a package manager for Windows).<br>
 To install Chocolatey please follow the below steps:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Launch a command prompt window (Win + r) and write <code>cmd</code> =
and press Enter.</p></li>
<li><p>Paste the following line into the cmd window and press enter to inst=
all and configure chocolatey.</p><pre><code class=3D"language-powershell" d=
ata-language=3D"powershell">@"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1=
.0\\powershell.exe" -NoProfile -InputFormat None -ExecutionPolicy Bypass ^
-Command "iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://bi=
tbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/wdp-developer-setup/raw/Powe=
rshell/InstallChocolatey.ps1'))"  &amp;&amp; ^
SET "PATH=3D%PATH%;%PROGRAMDATA%\chocoportable\bin"
</code></pre></li>
<li><p>(Optional) Execute the following command on your cmd window to refre=
sh the environment variables on your window: <code>refreshenv</code></p></l=
i>
</ul>
<h5 id=3D"user-content-note">Note:</h5>
<p>If you face errors running the above powershell command with an error st=
ating <code>The request was aborted: Could not create SSL/TLS secure channe=
l</code> then you are either missing the Westpac CA certificates from your =
user profile (which is concerning...) or you are running a build of Windows=
 10 that is defaulting to use a version of powershell which doesn't speak T=
LS1.2 by default.</p>
<p>To get around this you can run the following (significantly longer and n=
otably less secure) command to perform the initial chocolatey setup (You're=
 going to want this to all be on one line, so you may need to copy and past=
e this into notepad first):</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-powershell" data-language=3D"powershell">@"%Sy=
stemRoot%\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe" -NoProfile -I=
nputFormat None -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Command "add-type 'using System.Ne=
t;using System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates; public class TrustAl=
lCertsPolicy : ICertificatePolicy {public bool CheckValidationResult(Servic=
ePoint srvPoint, X509Certificate certificate,WebRequest request, int certif=
icateProblem) {return true;}}'; [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::Certifica=
tePolicy =3D New-Object TrustAllCertsPolicy; [System.Net.ServicePointManage=
r]::SecurityProtocol =3D [System.Net.SecurityProtocolType]'Ssl3,Tls,Tls11,T=
ls12'; iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://bitbu=
cket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/wdp-developer-setup/raw/Powersh=
ell/InstallChocolatey.ps1'))" &amp;&amp; SET "PATH=3D%PATH%;%PROGRAMDATA%\c=
hocoportable\bin"
</code></pre>
<h4 id=3D"user-content-prerequisites-installation">Prerequisites installati=
on</h4>
<p>Several prerequisite components need to be installed before using Mesh D=
eveloper Tools. These are:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Prerequisite</th>
<th>Chocolatey package name</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Git 2.x</td>
<td>git</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Python 3.12</td>
<td>python312</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>OpenSSL 1.0.2</td>
<td>openssl</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Apache Maven 3.9</td>
<td>maven</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Redhat OpenJDK 21</td>
<td>openjdk21</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Redhat OpenJDk 11</td>
<td>openjdk</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Node.js 20.12.2</td>
<td>nodejs</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Postman 7.36.1</td>
<td>postman</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>jq 1.5</td>
<td>jq</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>The following command (either from command/powershell prompt) will insta=
ll all prerequisites:</p>
<p>Note : The installation process takes quite a long time(on an average 30=
 minutes to install all tools).</p>
<pre><code>choco install -s=3Dartifactory openjdk21 maven git openssl pytho=
n312 nodejs postman jq
</code></pre>
<p>To install an individual tool, set the corresponding 'Chocolatey package=
 name' listed above.</p>
<pre><code>choco install -s=3Dartifactory &lt;package&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>For example, to install jdk11</p>
<pre><code>choco install -s=3Dartifactory openjdk
</code></pre>
<p><em>Note:</em> Alternatively to install Chocolatey from a powershell pro=
mpt</p>
<ul>
<li>Right click this <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projec=
ts/WDP2/repos/wdp-developer-setup/raw/installchocolatey.ps1?at=3Drefs/heads=
/master" rel=3D"nofollow">link</a> and select "Save target as" or "Save lin=
k as..." to save the file into a directory on your system.</li>
<li>Open PowerShell in the above directory and execute the script</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<h3 id=3D"MeshDeveloperTools-SpectralInstallation(ContractLinting)">Spectra=
l Installation (Contract Linting)</h3>
<p>It is recommended to install NodeJS and install Spectral CLI as a node m=
odules package irrespective of the developer profile (Java or NodeJS) as th=
e Mesh Developer tools requires Spectral to run Contract validations.</p>
<p>Spectral is a contract linting integrated with Mesh developer tools. Ref=
er <a href=3D"/display/MD/Contract+linting"> here </a>for more information =
on spectral and installation guidelines.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"MeshDeveloperTools-Installation">Installation</h2>
<p><!--
