ontent">
<h3 id=3D"user-content-mesh-developer-tools-installation">Mesh Developer To=
ols installation</h3>
<h4 id=3D"user-content-prerequisites">Prerequisites</h4>
<ul>
<li>Windows laptop (if you have a Mac please follow instructions here inste=
ad: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MD/Mac+OS+Setu=
p" rel=3D"nofollow">https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MD/Mac+OS=
+Setup</a>)</li>
<li>Please follow the Readme.md file located in the <a href=3D"https://bitb=
ucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/wdp-developer-setup/browse" re=
l=3D"nofollow">wdp-developer-setup Bitbucket repository</a> to install the =
prerequisite components.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"user-content-to-install-mesh-developer-tools">To install Mesh Dev=
eloper Tools</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-" data-language=3D"">pip install mesh-dev-tool=
s

</code></pre>
<h4 id=3D"user-content-to-update-mesh-developer-tools-to-the-latest-version=
">To update Mesh Developer Tools to the latest version</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-" data-language=3D"">mesh update

</code></pre>
<h4 id=3D"user-content-to-uninstall-mesh-developer-tools">To uninstall Mesh=
 Developer Tools</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash" data-language=3D"bash">pip uninstall mes=
h-dev-tools
</code></pre>
<p><em><strong>Note : All the above commands should be executed from a comm=
and prompt or a git bash terminal</strong></em></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"MeshDeveloperTools-GettingStartedGuide">Getting Started Guide</h2=
>
<p><!--
  ~ Copyright (c) 2014 by Mibex Software GmbH, Zurich, Switzerland.
  ~
  ~ All rights reserved.
  ~
