  --></p>
<div class=3D"file-macro-container include4confluence include4confluence-co=
ntent">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-panel panel" id=3D"include4confluence-bord=
er">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-panel-content-container ">
<div id=3D"include4confluence-markdown" class=3D"include4confluence-panel-c=
ontent">
<h3 id=3D"user-content-kickstarting-an-apilistener-component">Kickstarting =
an API/Listener Component:</h3>
<p>The basic flow to setup an API or listener component is: (Refer <a href=
=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/pypi-mesh-dev-=
tools/browse/Usage.md?at=3Drefs/heads/master" rel=3D"nofollow">Usage</a> fo=
r instructions on the mesh commands)</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Install Mesh Developer tools if you have not done so (<a href=3D"htt=
ps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Development Prerequisite)</a></p></li>
<li><p>Start a Windows or git-bash command prompt in your preferred local w=
orking directory.</p></li>
<li><p>Use 'mesh incubate' to create a incubator component or 'git clone' t=
o clone a real component repo you want to work on</p></li>
<li><p>Change directory to the newly cloned component directory.</p></li>
<li><p>Specify the API metadata and contract in the <code>swagger.yaml</cod=
e> or <code>webservice.wsdl</code></p></li>
<li><p>For API components only, generate the code using <code>mesh gencode<=
/code> - this supports Java and Node.js (not required for MQ Listener)</p><=
/li>
<li><p><code>mesh run</code> the code locally</p></li>
<li><p>Import the swagger spec to <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac=
.com.au/display/MESH/Test+the+Deployed+API+Using+Postman" rel=3D"nofollow">=
Postman</a> to test the running API</p></li>
<li><p>For <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/In=
cubator+Environment" rel=3D"nofollow">Incubator</a> components you can <cod=
e>mesh deploy</code> to the environment. Other components will deploy to de=
v automatically when changes are merged to master.</p></li>
</ol>
<p><em>Note: For usage of mesh commands such as <code>mesh incubate</code>,=
 <code>mesh gencode</code>, <code>mesh run</code> etc refer <a href=3D"http=
s://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/pypi-mesh-dev-tools/br=
owse/Usage.md?at=3Drefs/heads/master" rel=3D"nofollow">Usage</a></em></p>
<p>If you are getting below error while executing any of the mesh dev tools=
 commands , please follow the below instructions.</p>
<p><code>Error loading URL https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WD=
P2/repos/pypi-wdp-common/raw/wdp_common/wdp_config.yaml?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2=
Fconfig%2Fv1.5: HTTPSConnectionPool(host=3D'bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au', =
port=3D443): Max retries exceeded with url: /projects/WDP2/repos/pypi-wdp-c=
ommon/raw/wdp_common/wdp_config.yaml?at=3Drefs%2Fheads%2Fconfig%2Fv1.5 (Cau=
sed by SSLError(SSLError(1, '[SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate v=
erify failed (_ssl.c:852)'),))</code></p>
<p>Either reinstall the python package using below choco commands</p>
<pre><code>choco uninstall -s=3Dartifactory python

choco install -s=3Dartifactory python
</code></pre>
<p>or Run the following powershell commands</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-powershell" data-language=3D"powershell">    $=
caPath =3D Join-Path $env:ProgramData 'cacert.pem'
    Invoke-WebRequest -Uri 'https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifact=
ory/wdp-001_generic/au/com/westpac/security/certificates/20241001/cacert-20=
241001.pem' -OutFile $caPath -UseBasicParsing -ErrorAction 'Continue'
    [Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable('CURL_CA_BUNDLE', $caPath, [Envir=
onmentVariableTarget]::User)
</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"MeshDeveloperTools-UsageInstructions">Usage Instructions</h2>
